query: What are the stages of the Student Research Competition?
output:
The stages of the Student Research Competition are as follows: 

1. First Round: Abstract Submission - Students submit their research abstracts.
2. Second Round: Research Talk - Selected students from the first round give a short public presentation of their research, followed by a short Q&A session. 
3. Third Round: Grand Finals - The first-place winner in each category from the Student Research Competition will advance to the Grand Finals. Here, a different panel of judges evaluates the winners of all Student Research Competitions held during the year against each other via the web. Winners are then announced.
